Here, the notation formula_55 means that the sum is taken only over the values of formula_56 that are relatively prime to formula_18. The function formula_58 is a Dedekind sum.

The error after formula_59 terms is of the order of the next term, and formula_59 may be taken to be of the order of formula_61. As an example, Hardy and Ramanujan showed that formula_62 is the nearest integer to the sum of the first formula_63 terms of the series.

In 1937, Hans Rademacher was able to improve on Hardy and Ramanujan&#x27;s results by providing a convergent series expression for formula_12. It is
formula_65

The proof of Rademacher&#x27;s formula involves Ford circles, Farey sequences, modular symmetry and the Dedekind eta function.

It may be shown that the formula_18th term of Rademacher&#x27;s series is of the order
formula_67
so that the first term gives the Hardy–Ramanujan asymptotic approximation.
 published an elementary proof of the asymptotic formula for formula_12.

Techniques for implementing the Hardy–Ramanujan–Rademacher formula efficiently on a computer are discussed by , who shows that formula_12 can be computed in time formula_70 for any formula_71. This is near-optimal in that it matches the number of digits of the result. The largest value of the partition function computed exactly is formula_72, which has slightly more than 11 billion digits.

== Strict partition function ==

=== Definition and properties ===

A partition in which no part occurs more than once is called &quot;strict&quot;, or is said to be a partition &quot;into distinct parts&quot;. The function &quot;q&quot;(&quot;n&quot;) gives the number of these strict partitions of the given sum &quot;n&quot;. For example, &quot;q&quot;(3) = 2 because the partitions 3 and 1 + 2 are strict, while the third partition 1 + 1 + 1 of 3 has repeated parts. The number &quot;q&quot;(&quot;n&quot;) is also equal to the number of partitions of &quot;n&quot; in which only odd summands are permitted.

=== Generating function ===
